[resource]
script = ExtResource("1_qhpov")
reagent_id = "NaNO3"
title = "Sodium nitrate"
body = "[b]Basic facts[/b]
[table=2]
[cell]Formula:[/cell][cell]NaNO₃[/cell]
[cell]Molar mass:[/cell][cell]85 g/mol[/cell]
[cell]State at room temperature:[/cell][cell]White solid[/cell]
[/table]
[b]Formation reactions[/b]
NaOH + HNO₃ → NaNO₃ + H₂O  
Na₂O + 2HNO₃ → 2NaNO₃ + H₂O
[b]Important properties[/b]
• Ionic compound made of sodium and nitrate ions.  
• Highly soluble in water.  
• Oxidizing compound that can help substances burn.
[b]Where sodium nitrate is found[/b]
• In natural deposits such as Chile saltpeter.  
• Produced in chemical industry.
[b]Uses[/b]
• Fertilizers.  
• Used in food preservation.  
• Used in explosives and pyrotechnics.
[b]Safety[/b]
Can irritate skin and eyes.  
Large amounts may be harmful if swallowed."
